The paper deals with improving decoding algorithms for non-binary LDPC codes, which are commonly studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) communities. The proposed improvements involve reducing computational complexity, which is a common concern in the systems and control (cs.SI) community. The paper also discusses a re-selection scheme, which involves identifying periodic points and changing reliability information, which are topics commonly studied in the dynamical systems (cs.DS) community. Finally, the paper deals with error performance, which is a topic of interest in the computer communications (cs.CC) community.
